article.headline: Oklahoma St. 77, La Salle 62
article.story: OKLAHOMA CITY -- James Anderson scored 28 points, Marshall Moses added 18 points and Oklahoma State never trailed on its way to a 77-62 win against La Salle on Monday night at the All-College Classic. After La Salle (7-4) had cut a 16-point deficit in half, Anderson and Keiton Page led the Cowboys on a 12-2 run to restore the cushion. Anderson had a fast-break layup and a runner in the lane, then tipped the ball away to Page for a jumper in transition. Moses' free throw with 3:31 remaining put Oklahoma State (10-1) up 75-57. Rodney Green scored 22 points to lead the Explorers, but his 3-pointer to stop the Cowboys' surge was his team's only basket in the final 9 minutes. Page had 11 points and Obi Muonelo had eight points and 10 rebounds for the Cowboys.
